{"key":"processedPost-12789094","value":{"id":12789094,"first":12786544,"last":12790680,"when":1277300715,"utime":"06/23/10 04:45 PM","cleanedPost":"The reason for not rolling in vermiculite after first flush is because in the non-sterile environment of a fruiting chamber, contaminant spores naturally land on the cakes, but they can't germinate.&nbsp; However, if you protect them with a fresh layer of substrate(verm), they can easily germinate and ruin the cakes.<br />Rinse well between flushes, soak for a few hours, and then return to fruiting conditions, but it's best not to roll in verm.<br />RR"}}